Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Garbage Collection Algorithms Module

Provides advanced garbage collection (GC) strategies for memory management.

Features:
- Tracing (mark-sweep, mark-compact, copying)
- Reference counting (naive, cycle-detecting)
- Generational GC
- Concurrent and incremental GC
- Region-based and hybrid GC
- Pluggable GC interface
- Finalization, weak references, and barriers
- GC tuning, profiling, and debugging
- NUMA-aware and thread-local GC
- Error handling and fallback strategies
- AI/agent-friendly GC APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: GC Types and Interfaces
Type GCAlgorithm is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    collect as Function that takes no arguments returns GCStats
    configure as Function that takes config as GCConfig returns None
    stats as GCStats
    config as GCConfig
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GCStats is Dictionary with:
    collections as Integer
    collected_objects as Integer
    reclaimed_bytes as Integer
    pause_time as Float
    total_time as Float
    peak_memory as Integer
    error_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GCConfig is Dictionary with:
    gc_type as String
    threshold as Integer
    enable_concurrent as Boolean
    enable_incremental as Boolean
    enable_generational as Boolean
    enable_region as Boolean
    enable_finalization as Boolean
    enable_weak_refs as Boolean
    enable_profiling as Boolean
    enable_debugging as Boolean
    numa_node as Optional[Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core GC Implementations
Process called "create_tracing_gc" that takes config as GCConfig returns GCAlgorithm:
    Note: Tracing GC implementation
    Return GCAlgorithm with:
        name as "tracing"
        collect as tracing_collect
        configure as tracing_configure
        stats as GCStats with:
            collections as 0
            collected_objects as 0
            reclaimed_bytes as 0
            pause_time as 0.0
            total_time as 0.0
            peak_memory as 0
            error_count as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing
        config as config
        metadata as dictionary containing

